\date{2026-03-20}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/pull/72}
\import{stt-macros}
\title{Characterisation of the covariant action of #{\Hom}}
\tag{changelog}

\subtree{
\title{Summary}

\p{
Given a [precategory](Synthetic.Categories.Precategories) #{A}, i.e., a
[simplicial](stt-00AC) [Segal](stt-00AI) type, or more generally a
[left Segal](stt-00DA) type, we characterise the covariant action of the family
#{\Hom_A(a,{-})} for every #{a}, as postcomposition of morphisms:
[Characterisation of the covariant action of #{\Hom}](stt-00GB). As a corollary, we
obtain the [associative law of composition](stt-00G9). We also formalise
[right homotopies of morphisms](stt-00CH) and that composition in [Segal](stt-00AI)
types [is left and right unital](stt-00GA).
}
}

